column1: Note:  "nc" means "no coverage" or "no call" meaning a location that is not included in the coverage region for that kit.
Note:  "cb" means "coverage boundary" or a location near the edge of a coverage region.  Such locations are more likely to be false negatives.
Note:  "cbl" "cbu" or "cblu" are just inside a coverage boundary. Either upper lower or both in a one-base region
Note:  "cbl1" "cbu1" or "cblu1" are just one step outside a coverage boundary (which doesn't make sense). Either upper lower or both in a one-base gap
Note:  "in:" means an indel (insertion/deletion) usually specifically selected to be included.  Indels are otherwise less useful.
Note:  "(?+)" means this snp is presumed positive based on the presence of a lower snp
